---
title: Vegetable & Chicken Sausage Soup with Kale, Farro & Garlic Bread
description: No matter the weather, it’s tough not to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the culinary equivalent of a bear hug). Enter this hearty, soul-warming veggie rendition. It’s chock-full of goodness—that’s to say carrots, onion, crushed tomatoes, a bevy of Italian herbs and spices, chewy couscous, and tender kale. And because no good brothy bowl is complete without something delicious for dunking, we’re also throwing in a side of toasty, buttery garlic bread. Soup’s on!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6489ec150b7af205da01ba96-69260082.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6489ec150b7af205da01ba96.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegetable-chicken-sausage-soup-6489ec150b7af205da01ba96
course: main course
time required: 35m
nutrition:
  calories: 1100 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 127 g
  sugar: 28 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 13 g
  sodium: 2330 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%oz} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%oz}.

Place @farro{3/4%cup} and 3½ cups water in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Drain farro if necessary.

While farro cooks, pat @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken or sausage and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pot.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and carrots; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} and garlic into pot with veggies. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz}, @veggie stock concentrate{3}, 3 cups water, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until carrots are just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Use pot used for chicken or sausage here.

Once carrots are just softened, stir in kale. Cook until kale is wilted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir cooked farro into pot. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Once kale is wilted, stir in chicken or sausage.

Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1%tsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Toast baguette halves in a #toaster{} or under a #broiler{}. Then spread cut sides with garlic butter. Halve each piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Serve with garlic bread on the side.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.